OA1nbd: The good:Had 2 wisdom tooth extraction and braces. No issue at allThe bad:Crown:After braces I was recommended bonding or crown as my teeth still has gap because of peg lateral tooth. At first i choose bonding but it broke and stained. After that I was recommended crown. The doctor didnt explained fully about the crown at all. I asked the doctor if they shaving tooth a little and does the crown feel like real teeth. The doctor said yes. The doctor dont recommend veneer at other clinic (this clinic dont provide veneer). After crown installation, the crown feel too bulky and doesnt feel like real teeth at all. I made few adjustment after but still not feel comfortable after 7 months+. I even asked to pull out my crown but the doctor said the tooth will be very sensitive. Then I asked 2nd opinion from 3 doctor from 2 clinic (general dentist, endo and prosthodontist). They said the crown does not installed correctly. Then I went to prosthodontist to put new crown. Right now it feels like 90%, 95% real teeth.Filling (possible cause?)Had filling at clinic A. But after the filling, the tooth feel pain. Went to the clinic the doctor said need to wait few weeks. I was dumb and go to this clinic. The doctor said the filling is not enough. But after the filling, I think its the worst filling i had. I cant even floss the teeth. Then I went to the doctor to adjust the filling. After few days the pain goes away (maybe because of time) and can floss. But after few months, my teeth feel sensitive. Went to clinic A and they said my teeth had fracture. Had to do large filling because of that. Few months after my teeth still feel sensitive. Clinic A said because there microleakage. The doctor redo the filling but after a week still feel sensitive. The doctor suggest do root canal or endo. I went to endo and he said only need to do filing. So far my teeth feel 85% ok. The endo said need to wait few weeks
